{
  "text": "Furthermore, the present results may have implications for the striatal site of action of systemically administered NMDA-antagonists: dizocilpine, a potent NMDA-antagonist reversed neuroleptic-induced catalepsy [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Elliott etal., 1990b) and NMDA given systemically in combination with haloperidol potentiated the cataleptogenic effects of haloperidol [CITATION_3] . From the present results one may conclude that within the CP the anti-cataleptic effects of systemically administered NMDA antagonists is mediated mainly through quinolinic acidsensitive projection neurons in the lateral CP.",
